g player chooses a set of creatures that will block and pays any costs they require to block. Only untapped creatures can block, but blocking doesn\rquote 
t cause creatures to tap. Other effects may also affect whether or not a set of creatures could block. See rule 500, \'93Legal Attacks and Blocks.\'94
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Declare Blockers Step
\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
