your library in any order and the rest on top of your library in any order.\'94 See rule 502.36, \'93Scry.\'94}{\b 
\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Sealed-Deck
\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
For sealed deck or draft play, only forty cards are required in a deck, and a player may use as many duplicates of a card as he or she has. E
ach player still needs small items to represent any tokens and counters, and some way to clearly track life totals. See rule 100.3.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Search
\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {If you\rquote 
re required to search a zone not revealed to all players for cards of a given quality, such as type or color, you aren\rquote t required to find some or all of those cards even if they\rquote 
re present; however, if you do choose to find cards, you must reveal those cards to all players. Even if you don\rquote t find any cards, you are still considered to have searched the zone.
\par      If you\rquote re simply searching for a quantity of cards, such as \'93a card\'94 or \'93three cards,\'94 you must find that many cards (or as many as possible). These cards often aren\rquote t revealed.
\par }\pard\plain \s28\ql \li400\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin400\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b Example:}{ If an effect causes you to search a player\rquote s library for all duplica
tes of a particular card and remove them from the game, you may choose to leave some of them alone, but if an effect causes you to search your library for three cards and it contains at least three, you can\rquote t choose less than three.
\par }\pard\plain \s27\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Set Aside
