 Paying a card\rquote s splice cost follows the rules for paying additional costs in rules 409.1b and 409.1f\endash h.
\par      You can\rquote t choose to use a splice ability if you can\rquote t make the required choices (targets, etc.) for that card\rquote s instructions. You can\rquote t splice any one card onto the same spell more than once. If you\rquote 
re splicing more than one card onto a spell, reveal them all at once and choose the order in which their instructions will be followed. The instructions on the main spell have to be followed first.
\par      The spell has the characteristics of the main spell, plus the text boxes of each of the spliced cards. The spell doesn\rquote t gain any other characteristics (name, mana cost, color, supertypes, types, subtypes, etc.) of the spliced cards.
\par      Choose targets for the added text normally (see rule 409.1c). Note that a spell with one or more targets will be countered if all of its targets are illegal on resolution.
\par      The spell loses any splice changes once it leaves the stack (e.g. when it\rquote s countered, it\rquote s removed from the game, or it resolves).
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Split Cards
