re playing. While it\rquote s on the stack, the other side is ignored completely. See rule 505, \'93Split Cards.\'94
\par      Split cards have two mana costs with different colors of mana in them. That means they are multicolored cards, except while they\rquote re on the stack.
\par      If an effect tells you to name a card, you must name all of a split card\rquote s names.
\par      Effects that ask for a split card\rquote s characteristic get both answers. Effects that ask if a split card\rquote s characteristic matches a given value get only one answer. This answer is \'93yes\'94 if either side of the split card matches
 the given value.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s26\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Stack
